@{
    ViewBag.Title = "ATA";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Products.cshtml";
}
<div class="product-policy">
    <div id="personalization">
        <h1>Product Availability </h1>
        <p>
            ATA reserves the right to change any or all prices and to eliminate items without advance notice or substitute revised materials for those orders. If you need assistance locating a product or have questions regarding the ATA Store,
            please call 800-282-5463 or email  <a href="mailto:orders@trucking.org">orders@trucking.org</a>.

        </p>
    </div>
    <div id="payment">
        <h1>Product Personalization</h1>

        <h4>SHIPPING POLICY FOR PERSONALIZED PRODUCTS</h4>
        <p>
            Many of our products are available with personalization. Please allow additional time for orders including product personalization.
        </p>
        <h4>HOW TO PERSONALIZE A PRODUCT</h4>
        <p>
            Select the customizable product you are interested in ordering. Then click on the "Custom" box. This will display the pricing for this product. Now click on the "add to cart" button. At this point, if you are not already logged on to the ATA Store, you will be asked to log in. If you have an existing account, you would use your standard login information. However, if you are not an member and have also never previously ordered product through the ATA Store, you would then need to register.
        </p>
        <p>
            Once you are successfully logged in, you will then be directed to a page which provides all the text fields available for customization. Fill out the fields which correspond with your personalization needs and then click the "create proof" button. Once you do so, your proof will be automatically generated and presented to you for review. To inspect the proof up close, click the "View Sample PDF" link just below the product image and wait ten to twenty seconds for the proof PDF to load. If you wish to then add this product to your order, simply click the "add to order" button and proceed with your order. Please note that all customized product sales are final. You are responsible for reviewing your customized content.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h1>Payment </h1>
        <p>
            As of December 1st, 2015, all ATA Store orders must be paid at time of purchase. VISA, MasterCard and American Express are all accepted. 
            <!--For check orders, please verify shipping and applicable tax before mailing payment.-->
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
